40static const int ALL = 0;
41static const int EVEN = 1;
42static const int ODD = 2;
43
44static bool CorrectErrors(ByteArray& codewordBytes, int start, int dataCodewords, int ecCodewords, int mode)
45{
46 int codewords = dataCodewords + ecCodewords;
47
48 // in EVEN or ODD mode only half the codewords
49 int divisor = mode == ALL ? 1 : 2;
50
51 // First read into an array of ints
52 std::vector<int> codewordsInts(codewords / divisor, 0);
53 for (int i = 0; i < codewords; i++) {
54 if ((mode == ALL) || (i % 2 == (mode - 1))) {
55 codewordsInts[i / divisor] = codewordBytes[i + start];
56 }
57 }
58
59 if (!ReedSolomonDecoder::Decode(GenericGF::MaxiCodeField64(), codewordsInts, ecCodewords / divisor))
60 return false;
61
62 // Copy back into array of bytes -- only need to worry about the bytes that were data
63 // We don't care about errors in the error-correction codewords
64 for (int i = 0; i < dataCodewords; i++) {
65 if ((mode == ALL) || (i % 2 == (mode - 1))) {
66 codewordBytes[i + start] = static_cast<uint8_t>(codewordsInts[i / divisor]);
67 }
68 }
69 return true;
70}

138 static int GetBit(int bit, const ByteArray& bytes)
139 {
140 bit--;
141 return (bytes[bit / 6] & (1 << (5 - (bit % 6)))) == 0 ? 0 : 1;
142 }
143
144 static int GetInt(const ByteArray& bytes, const ByteArray& x)
145 {
146 int len = Size(x);
147 int val = 0;
148 for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
149 val += GetBit(x[i], bytes) << (len - i - 1);
150 }
151 return val;
152 }
153
154 static int GetPostCode2(const ByteArray& bytes)
155 {
156 return GetInt(bytes, { 33, 34, 35, 36, 25, 26, 27, 28, 29, 30, 19, 20, 21, 22, 23, 24, 13, 14, 15, 16, 17, 18, 7, 8, 9, 10, 11, 12, 1, 2 });
157 }
158
159 static int GetPostCode2Length(const ByteArray& bytes) {
160 return GetInt(bytes, { 39, 40, 41, 42, 31, 32 });
161 }
162
163 static std::string GetPostCode3(const ByteArray& bytes)
164 {
165 return {
166 CHARSETS[0].at(GetInt(bytes, { 39, 40, 41, 42, 31, 32 })),
167 CHARSETS[0].at(GetInt(bytes, { 33, 34, 35, 36, 25, 26 })),
168 CHARSETS[0].at(GetInt(bytes, { 27, 28, 29, 30, 19, 20 })),
169 CHARSETS[0].at(GetInt(bytes, { 21, 22, 23, 24, 13, 14 })),
170 CHARSETS[0].at(GetInt(bytes, { 15, 16, 17, 18, 7, 8 })),
171 CHARSETS[0].at(GetInt(bytes, { 9, 10, 11, 12, 1, 2 })),
172 };
173 }

175
176 static std::string ToString(int x, int width)
177 {
178 std::stringstream buf;
179 buf << std::setw(width) << std::setfill('0') << x;
180 return buf.str();
181 }
182
183 static int GetCountry(const ByteArray& bytes)
184 {
185 return GetInt(bytes, { 53, 54, 43, 44, 45, 46, 47, 48, 37, 38 });
186 }
187
188 static int GetServiceClass(const ByteArray& bytes)
189 {
190 return GetInt(bytes, { 55, 56, 57, 58, 59, 60, 49, 50, 51, 52 });
191 }
192
193 static std::string GetMessage(const ByteArray& bytes, int start, int len)
194 {
195 std::string sb;
196 int shift = -1;
197 int set = 0;
198 int lastset = 0;
199 for (int i = start; i < start + len; i++) {
200 char c = CHARSETS[set].at(bytes[i]);
201 switch (c) {
202 case LCHA:
203 set = 0;
204 shift = -1;
205 break;
206 case LCHB:
207 set = 1;
208 shift = -1;
209 break;
210 case SHI0:
211 case SHI1:
212 case SHI2:
213 case SHI3:
214 case SHI4:
215 lastset = set;
216 set = c - SHI0;
217 shift = 1;
218 break;
219 case TWSA:
220 lastset = set;
221 set = 0;
222 shift = 2;
223 break;
224 case TRSA:
225 lastset = set;
226 set = 0;
227 shift = 3;
228 break;
229 case NS:
230 sb.append(ToString((bytes[i+1] << 24) + (bytes[i+2] << 18) + (bytes[i+3] << 12) + (bytes[i+4] << 6) + bytes[i+5], 9));
231 i += 5;
232 break;
233 case LOCK:
234 shift = -1;
235 break;
236 default:
237 sb.push_back(c);
238 }
239 if (shift-- == 0) {
240 set = lastset;
241 }
242 }
243 while (sb.length() > 0 && sb.at(sb.length() - 1) == PAD) {
244 sb.resize(sb.length() - 1);
245 }
246 return sb;
247 }
248
249 static DecoderResult Decode(ByteArray&& bytes, int mode)
250 {
251 std::string result;
252 result.reserve(144);
253 switch (mode) {
254 case 2:
255 case 3: {
256 auto postcode = mode == 2 ? ToString(GetPostCode2(bytes), GetPostCode2Length(bytes)) : GetPostCode3(bytes);
257 auto country = ToString(GetCountry(bytes), 3);
258 auto service = ToString(GetServiceClass(bytes), 3);
259 result.append(GetMessage(bytes, 10, 84));
260 if (result.compare(0, 7, std::string("[)>") + RS + std::string("01") + GS) == 0) {
261 result.insert(9, postcode + GS + country + GS + service + GS);
262 }
263 else {
264 result.insert(0, postcode + GS + country + GS + service + GS);
265 }
266 break;
267 }
268 case 4:
269 result.append(GetMessage(bytes, 1, 93));
270 break;
271 case 5:
272 result.append(GetMessage(bytes, 1, 77));
273 break;
274 }
275 return DecoderResult(std::move(bytes), TextDecoder::FromLatin1(result)).setEcLevel(std::to_wstring(mode)); // really???
276 }

282DecoderResult
283Decoder::Decode(const BitMatrix& bits)
284{
285 ByteArray codewords = BitMatrixParser::ReadCodewords(bits);
286
287 if (!CorrectErrors(codewords, 0, 10, 10, ALL)) {
288 return DecodeStatus::ChecksumError;
289 }
290 int mode = codewords[0] & 0x0F;
291 ByteArray datawords;
292 switch (mode) {
293 case 2:
294 case 3:
295 case 4:
296 if (CorrectErrors(codewords, 20, 84, 40, EVEN) && CorrectErrors(codewords, 20, 84, 40, ODD)) {
297 datawords.resize(94, 0);
298 }
299 else {
300 return DecodeStatus::ChecksumError;
301 }
302 break;
303 case 5:
304 if (CorrectErrors(codewords, 20, 68, 56, EVEN) && CorrectErrors(codewords, 20, 68, 56, ODD)) {
305 datawords.resize(78, 0);
306 }
307 else {
308 return DecodeStatus::ChecksumError;
309 }
310 break;
311 default:
312 return DecodeStatus::FormatError;
313 }
314
315 std::copy_n(codewords.begin(), 10, datawords.begin());
316 std::copy_n(codewords.begin() + 20, datawords.size() - 10, datawords.begin() + 10);
317
318 return DecodedBitStreamParser::Decode(std::move(datawords), mode);
319}
